##Netizens are wishing it an early closure of the hospital, "Shelter Hospital" is what?

Micro Signal China Business Journal

Function introduction, grow in step with Chinese enterprises, talk with business leaders, spread business ideals, serve business people, "China Business News" control of the absolute voice of Chinese business.

The following article comes from our remedial class, the author of the Committee on Remedial Class

Adult 100,000 Whys, rediscover your curiosity about the world

Square dancing, Yoga, Tai Chi, studying for exams... Every day we can learn from social media about the daily life of the patients in Wuhan's "Shelter Hospital" . These seemingly ordinary activities, but for the intense anti-epidemic work has brought a glimmer of vitality and inspiration.

On the evening of February 3, Wuhan announced that it would build a "shelter hospital" at the Wuhan International Convention and Exhibition Centre, a Wembley Arena and a living room to treat patients with new pneumonia.

Later, with the increase of confirmed patients, after the first batch of "shelter hospitals" put into use, large and small "shelter hospitals" have been built one after another. It is reported that Wuhan has fully opened 12 shelter hospitals, the city's shelter hospital plan has more than 20,000 beds.

What is a shelter hospital?

"shelter" is not the name of the hospital, but a modular field medical equipment. Field hospitals are not unfamiliar, mainly used in the war to treat the wounded, and "Shelter Hospital" is a mobile by a shelter composed of the field hospital.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
We can think of the boxes as Lego blocks, some for surgery, x-rays, sterilization, storage of drugs and medical equipment, and so on, these are called functional boxes.

Some are used to power and water the functional shelter, to ensure their normal operation, these are the technical support shelter.

The functional shelter and the technical support shelter are connected to the tunnel shelter.

Together with the tents for the sick and wounded and the vehicles for transport, it forms a complete "shelter hospital. ".

From the form of the Shelter Hospital, we can see that compared with the traditional tent-based field hospital, the shelter hospital should be more flexible, mobile, medical conditions are more perfect, more able to adapt to wartime needs.

Therefore, from the 1960s, the United States first began to research and application of medical shelter began, the United Kingdom, Germany, France and other countries have also carried out research.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
In the 1990s, our army began to research and apply medical shelter. Although it started relatively late, it developed rapidly.

The first-generation Shelter Hospital system is still basically equipped with hospital diagnosis and treatment functions. The Ward Unit can deploy 100 beds and perform 75 operations around the clock. In the second generation, 150-200 beds have been deployed, 300-400 people can be injured or sick in the day and night, and functions such as remote consultation and CBRN defense have been added. The equipment is more advanced, the combination is more flexible, and the rescue capacity has been greatly improved.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Of course, upgrades to the medical shelter system continue. The argumentation design of the third-generation Shelter Hospital system has been greatly improved in the level of information, technical support, staffing and so on.

Used in earthquake rescue

Although the shelter hospital originated in the war, but not only for military operations, but also in emergency rescue operations such as disaster relief. In the Wenchuan County earthquake, Yushu earthquake rescue, the shelter hospital played a vital role.

Time is of the essence in emergency rescue and disaster relief. The advantages of the flexible and easy-to-assemble feature of the Shelter Hospital were brought into play at this time.

Let's take the x-ray shelter as an example. It is a kind of functional shelter, which is mainly used to diagnose patients.

In the immediate aftermath of the Wenchuan County earthquake, it took just an hour and a half for the 12 shelters and auxiliary health tents to enter the site, spread out, connect, arrange the equipment, install the lines, and finally start seeing patients.

Of course, no matter how quickly it's assembled, the medical function can't keep up. So, what is the medical standard of the Shelter Hospital?

The Sparrow may be small, but it has all the essentials. Although the shelter hospitals are all temporary, they have all the necessary equipment.

Layout Plan of x-ray shelter

▼

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The medical level of a complete shelter hospital can not be ignored. It is reported that the shelter hospital after the launch is equivalent to a second-class hospital. More than 30,000 patients were treated, more than 2,400 were treated, and more than 1,400 operations were performed in the 150 days after the 2010 Yushu earthquake.

Why is the bunker hospital being used in this outbreak?

After getting a general idea of the shelter hospital, let's go back to the several shelter hospitals built in Wuhan during the outbreak.

Wang Chen, vice president of the Chinese Academy of Engineering and President of the Chinese Academy of Medical Sciences, told reporters that the large-scale "shelter hospital" is different from the field mobile hospitals used in wartime or earthquake relief. It has not been used in the past, and it is an important measure of public health prevention and control and medical treatment in China.

In fact, the construction of several Wuhan "Shelter Hospital" and the traditional sense of the "shelter hospital" slightly different, more is the use of the core of the shelter hospital.

From the news reports, we can see that most of the shelter hospitals currently in use or under construction are renovation of the existing stadiums, convention and exhibition centers and other public facilities with more open space.

Wuhan Sports Center Stadium

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Photo: Weibo@xinhua View

As we all know, isolation of the source of infection is essential to control the development of the epidemic, and the shelter hospital is being renovated at a rapid pace, taking at least 24 hours to complete, the aim of isolating the infectious source and curing the patient can be achieved in a short time.

In addition, different from the traditional ward, the ward in the shelter hospital is open, and patients are concentrated in a unified site, which is more conducive to the medical staff to take care of patients and carry out work.

According to the video uploaded to the social networking site by the patients in the Shelter Hospital, the medical staff have to measure the patients several times a day and record the patients'conditions and data, centralized care allows health care workers to perform these tasks quickly and efficiently.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Photo: Video Clip from weibo@people.com.cn

The open space also allows medical staff to be the first time to find changes in patients, once the deterioration of the phenomenon, can be timely treatment, or sent to designated hospitals for treatment.

Of course, many people also worry about whether intensive care can lead to cross-infection.

In fact, the shelter hospital has been admitted to the treatment of patients with mild illness has been confirmed, under normal circumstances there will not be cross-infection.

Of course, Wang Chen also said in an interview with media reporters that the conditions of a shelter hospital are indeed not as complete as those of a regular hospital, but it is basically sufficient for patients with mild illness, mainly to solve the problems of expanding the capacity of admission and isolating the source of infection.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
PICTURE: Video Clip from Weibo@cctv News

He also admitted that in the current situation, although the building of a shelter hospital is not the best way, but in the absence of more perfect methods appear, is the critical period to resolve the contradictions of the practical solution.

Hope is like netizen wish, the Hospital of shelter cabin can close a hospital as soon as possible.
